SIMPLE: inexpiable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexpiable
<hw>In*ex"pi*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexpiabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inexpiable</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Expiable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Admitting of no expiation, atonement, or
satisfaction; <as>as, an <ex>inexpiable</ex> crime or
offense</as>.</def> <rj><au>Pomfret.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Incapable of being mollified or appeased;
relentless; implacable.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inexpiable</xex> hate.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They are at <qex>inexpiable</qex> war with all establishments.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexpiableness</ent>⟦br⟧
